The scenes of nature
that I have in my bedroom

00:37:13.920 --> 00:37:17.480 align:middle line:84%
were painted by my husband,
and that really feeds my soul.

00:37:17.480 --> 00:37:19.590 align:middle line:90%
My bed was made by my husband.

00:37:19.590 --> 00:37:21.270 align:middle line:84%
And when I'm in it,
not only does it

00:37:21.270 --> 00:37:22.880 align:middle line:90%
carry the love of my husband.

00:37:22.880 --> 00:37:26.900 align:middle line:84%
But it also carries a sense of
strength and stability for me.

00:37:26.900 --> 00:37:30.360 align:middle line:84%
So many people get into bed
and they turn the TV on.

00:37:30.360 --> 00:37:33.020 align:middle line:84%
And it really-- it takes
them out of their life.

00:37:33.020 --> 00:37:34.610 align:middle line:90%
I don't have a TV in my bedroom.

00:37:34.610 --> 00:37:37.740 align:middle line:84%
I don't have a phone,
the reason being it

00:37:37.740 --> 00:37:41.680 align:middle line:84%
was so easy to pick that phone
up and start doing business.

00:37:41.680 --> 00:37:44.190 align:middle line:84%
And that place that was a
sanctuary all of a sudden

00:37:44.190 --> 00:37:45.540 align:middle line:90%
wasn't a sanctuary.

00:37:45.540 --> 00:37:49.730 align:middle line:84%
Even an alarm clock can
pull you away from yourself.

00:37:49.730 --> 00:37:51.290 align:middle line:84%
When you wake up first
thing in the morning

00:37:51.290 --> 00:37:55.050 align:middle line:84%
to that jangling sound, it
sets an energy for the day.

00:37:55.050 --> 00:37:57.890 align:middle line:84%
How much better it is
to awake to soft music,

00:37:57.890 --> 00:38:02.290 align:middle line:84%
for example, or to awake to
the sun coming in your window.

00:38:02.290 --> 00:38:05.390 align:middle line:84%
As much as possible, it's
important to have space

00:38:05.390 --> 00:38:07.680 align:middle line:84%
underneath the bed to
have a sense of clarity,

00:38:07.680 --> 00:38:09.570 align:middle line:90%
even if it can't be seen.

00:38:09.570 --> 00:38:12.750 align:middle line:84%
Our subconscious mind is aware
that directly beneath our body

00:38:12.750 --> 00:38:14.670 align:middle line:90%
is a lot of disorganization.

00:38:14.670 --> 00:38:16.460 align:middle line:84%
Every single thing
in your bedroom

00:38:16.460 --> 00:38:19.450 align:middle line:84%
should be something
you love, or you use.

00:38:19.450 --> 00:38:21.230 align:middle line:90%
It should have meaning to you.

00:38:21.230 --> 00:38:23.820 align:middle line:84%
If you focus on things
that are beautiful,

00:38:23.820 --> 00:38:27.760 align:middle line:84%
you will see beauty around you,
and the space that you live in

00:38:27.760 --> 00:38:31.060 align:middle line:84%
can be a template for
what you desire in life.

00:38:31.060 --> 00:38:33.980 align:middle line:84%
If you desire to have
more peace in your life,

00:38:33.980 --> 00:38:36.916 align:middle line:84%
create an environment
that feels peaceful.

00:38:36.916 --> 00:38:38.950 align:middle line:84%
If you want more
adventure in your life,

00:38:38.950 --> 00:38:42.790 align:middle line:84%
create an environment
that feels adventuresome.

00:38:42.790 --> 00:38:45.790 align:middle line:84%
I think of my bedroom
as a sacred space.

00:38:45.790 --> 00:38:48.480 align:middle line:84%
It's a place for rejuvenation,
a place for healing,

00:38:48.480 --> 00:38:53.518 align:middle line:84%
a place where I refuel, where
I can go and feed my soul,

00:38:53.518 --> 00:38:56.326 align:middle line:90%
where I can go and do nothing.

00:38:56.326 --> 00:38:57.730 align:middle line:84%
And then that nothing
is everything.

00:38:57.730 --> 00:39:00.070 align:middle line:90%


00:39:00.070 --> 00:39:02.880 align:middle line:10%
So you just shared with
me that when you were asked

00:39:02.880 --> 00:39:06.330 align:middle line:10%
on the Oprah Show that was the
first time that you had taught

00:39:06.330 --> 00:39:08.580 align:middle line:10%
in the United
States, or that you

00:39:08.580 --> 00:39:09.900 align:middle line:10%
presented in the United States.

00:39:09.900 --> 00:39:12.220 align:middle line:10%
Well, here's what was amazing.

00:39:12.220 --> 00:39:15.240 align:middle line:10%
I like I said, I've taught in
25 countries around the world.

00:39:15.240 --> 00:39:17.940 align:middle line:10%
And I would always go
where people asked me.

00:39:17.940 --> 00:39:20.967 align:middle line:10%
And I would only get asked
to little tiny countries

00:39:20.967 --> 00:39:21.800 align:middle line:10%
in the middle of nowhere.

00:39:21.800 --> 00:39:24.800 align:middle line:10%
But I never got asked to
teach in the United States.

00:39:24.800 --> 00:39:26.960 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, it's
just so strange

00:39:26.960 --> 00:39:28.310 align:middle line:90%
that it's my own country.

00:39:28.310 --> 00:39:29.570 align:middle line:90%
But I'm not been asked here.

00:39:29.570 --> 00:39:32.670 align:middle line:84%
So I did a very deep
meditation to look

00:39:32.670 --> 00:39:34.350 align:middle line:90%
and see what's that all about.

00:39:34.350 --> 00:39:37.990 align:middle line:84%
And I saw that I was
afraid that the man who

00:39:37.990 --> 00:39:40.170 align:middle line:84%
shot me, because at
that point he was-- I

00:39:40.170 --> 00:39:41.740 align:middle line:90%
mean he wasn't in jail.

00:39:41.740 --> 00:39:43.605 align:middle line:84%
That he would find me,
and that he would--

00:39:43.605 --> 00:39:46.610 align:middle line:84%
he would-- because he
had said, I'll get you.

00:39:46.610 --> 00:39:48.170 align:middle line:90%
He said that to you--

00:39:48.170 --> 00:39:50.120 align:middle line:84%
Someone told me he
had-- the policeman

00:39:50.120 --> 00:39:51.350 align:middle line:84%
told me had said that.
So--

00:39:51.350 --> 00:39:52.270 align:middle line:90%
When he was arrested?

00:39:52.270 --> 00:39:53.170 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:39:53.170 --> 00:39:55.490 align:middle line:90%
And as he was going off to jail.

00:39:55.490 --> 00:39:56.930 align:middle line:84%
Yeah.
And then he got out.

00:39:56.930 --> 00:39:58.780 align:middle line:90%
But so I was afraid.

00:39:58.780 --> 00:40:01.010 align:middle line:84%
But I didn't know
that I was afraid.

00:40:01.010 --> 00:40:05.250 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, I do not want
to live my life in fear.

00:40:05.250 --> 00:40:07.430 align:middle line:90%
And so I made a stand.

00:40:07.430 --> 00:40:08.900 align:middle line:84%
I just-- I could
remember so clearly.

00:40:08.900 --> 00:40:11.420 align:middle line:84%
I stood up at my
home office, my desk.

00:40:11.420 --> 00:40:15.030 align:middle line:90%
And I said, I face this.

00:40:15.030 --> 00:40:19.300 align:middle line:84%
And probably within an hour,
I got a telephone call from

00:40:19.300 --> 00:40:21.490 align:middle line:90%
the producer of the Oprah Show.

00:40:21.490 --> 00:40:23.880 align:middle line:90%
And I thought, oh my gosh.

00:40:23.880 --> 00:40:24.750 align:middle line:90%
I declared.

00:40:24.750 --> 00:40:26.220 align:middle line:90%
I'm ready to face my fear.

00:40:26.220 --> 00:40:29.370 align:middle line:84%
But I'm thinking, couldn't be
like a little local TV show?

00:40:29.370 --> 00:40:31.180 align:middle line:84%
Why does it have
to be like Oprah?

00:40:31.180 --> 00:40:32.290 align:middle line:90%
And then I'm back-pedalling.

00:40:32.290 --> 00:40:33.709 align:middle line:84%
And I said, OK.
I'll come on.

00:40:33.709 --> 00:40:36.020 align:middle line:84%
But I will not talk
about getting shot.

00:40:36.020 --> 00:40:37.450 align:middle line:90%
Because my name's different now.

00:40:37.450 --> 00:40:40.695 align:middle line:84%
And people said, friends said,
no mass murderer is going

00:40:40.695 --> 00:40:41.930 align:middle line:90%
to be watching Oprah anyway.

00:40:41.930 --> 00:40:42.690 align:middle line:90%
So don't worry.

00:40:42.690 --> 00:40:45.210 align:middle line:84%
Well, you couldn't be so
sure, because you had a child.

00:40:45.210 --> 00:40:46.230 align:middle line:90%
I did have a child.

00:40:46.230 --> 00:40:49.470 align:middle line:84%
And I was-- and I think when I
was facing my fear and looking,

00:40:49.470 --> 00:40:51.900 align:middle line:84%
my fear was as
much for her as it

00:40:51.900 --> 00:40:53.370 align:middle line:90%
was for me, probably more so.

00:40:53.370 --> 00:40:57.750 align:middle line:84%
Because at the point was
very protective of her.

00:40:57.750 --> 00:40:58.460 align:middle line:90%
But I went.

00:40:58.460 --> 00:41:01.850 align:middle line:90%
And-- and it was scary.

00:41:01.850 --> 00:41:03.710 align:middle line:90%
But I'm so glad that I did it.

00:41:03.710 --> 00:41:04.470 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:41:04.470 --> 00:41:05.170 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:41:05.170 --> 00:41:09.650 align:middle line:84%
So you were teaching then
about-- about space clearing.

00:41:09.650 --> 00:41:11.910 align:middle line:84%
You were teaching about how
to set up your environment.

00:41:11.910 --> 00:41:14.557 align:middle line:84%
And you were using your
dream work at that time.

00:41:14.557 --> 00:41:16.290 align:middle line:84%
And that was what you were
brought on the Oprah Show

00:41:16.290 --> 00:41:17.950 align:middle line:90%
for, right?

00:41:17.950 --> 00:41:20.960 align:middle line:84%
That-- I've been on the
Oprah show several times.

00:41:20.960 --> 00:41:26.240 align:middle line:84%
That particular show was about
living life with passion.

00:41:26.240 --> 00:41:30.150 align:middle line:84%
So it was-- and I
can admit this now.

00:41:30.150 --> 00:41:31.820 align:middle line:90%
Because it was a long time ago.

00:41:31.820 --> 00:41:35.820 align:middle line:84%
I didn't actually-- there was
like the five-point passion.

00:41:35.820 --> 00:41:37.660 align:middle line:84%
And a friend of mine
who was a journalist

00:41:37.660 --> 00:41:41.210 align:middle line:84%
had written up this, Denise
Linn's five points for passion.

00:41:41.210 --> 00:41:43.360 align:middle line:84%
But she was a friend, and
she made up the five points.

00:41:43.360 --> 00:41:44.960 align:middle line:90%
But she didn't ask me.

00:41:44.960 --> 00:41:46.940 align:middle line:84%
She said, Oh I knew it
would be OK with you.

00:41:46.940 --> 00:41:48.790 align:middle line:90%
So they found this article.

00:41:48.790 --> 00:41:50.340 align:middle line:90%
And they liked it so much.

00:41:50.340 --> 00:41:52.320 align:middle line:84%
And they said, well
you know, come and talk

00:41:52.320 --> 00:41:53.270 align:middle line:90%
about your five points.

00:41:53.270 --> 00:41:55.470 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well
what five points?

00:41:55.470 --> 00:41:56.874 align:middle line:84%
And they said it
was in this article.

00:41:56.874 --> 00:41:58.760 align:middle line:84%
I'm like OK.
I'll talk about--

00:41:58.760 --> 00:42:00.704 align:middle line:84%
You've had such
a miraculous life.

00:42:00.704 --> 00:42:01.970 align:middle line:84%
I mean there's people
who have written

00:42:01.970 --> 00:42:04.580 align:middle line:84%
volumes and wanted to be
on Oprah all of their life,

00:42:04.580 --> 00:42:05.850 align:middle line:90%
and you're--

00:42:05.850 --> 00:42:07.810 align:middle line:84%
But I think it was
the universe saying,

00:42:07.810 --> 00:42:10.580 align:middle line:84%
you have declared to
the creator that you

00:42:10.580 --> 00:42:12.320 align:middle line:90%
are ready to face this fear.

00:42:12.320 --> 00:42:14.240 align:middle line:90%
So step up.

00:42:14.240 --> 00:42:18.030 align:middle line:84%
I mean to me, I think,
because it wasn't my plan.

00:42:18.030 --> 00:42:20.730 align:middle line:84%
I didn't even-- I mean, I
was surprised about this.

00:42:20.730 --> 00:42:23.290 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know about the
article until that point.

00:42:23.290 --> 00:42:26.701 align:middle line:84%
Well, that just shows that you
were in such a miraculous place

00:42:26.701 --> 00:42:27.400 align:middle line:90%
in your life.

00:42:27.400 --> 00:42:29.700 align:middle line:84%
And you're teaching through
all of your stories,

00:42:29.700 --> 00:42:30.740 align:middle line:90%
which I absolutely love.

00:42:30.740 --> 00:42:35.030 align:middle line:84%
But there's another incredible
example of how you ultimately

00:42:35.030 --> 00:42:37.960 align:middle line:84%
have used forgiveness so many
different times in your life,

00:42:37.960 --> 00:42:39.340 align:middle line:90%
with your father.

00:42:39.340 --> 00:42:42.590 align:middle line:84%
Now your parents, you said,
you didn't communicate that

00:42:42.590 --> 00:42:47.390 align:middle line:84%
much with them after college?
-No.

00:42:47.390 --> 00:42:50.240 align:middle line:84%
It was-- just to
take a step back.

00:42:50.240 --> 00:42:52.330 align:middle line:90%
My mother was very violent.

00:42:52.330 --> 00:42:54.180 align:middle line:90%
She was paranoid schizophrenic.

00:42:54.180 --> 00:42:56.937 align:middle line:84%
She-- they put her-- the
first time they put her

00:42:56.937 --> 00:42:58.570 align:middle line:84%
in a mental hospital, it
was because they thought

00:42:58.570 --> 00:42:59.403 align:middle line:90%
she was going to kill me.

00:42:59.403 --> 00:43:02.320 align:middle line:90%
She was very violent.

00:43:02.320 --> 00:43:03.770 align:middle line:90%
And it was scary.

00:43:03.770 --> 00:43:05.830 align:middle line:84%
You know, often I'd sleep
in the bathtub at night,

00:43:05.830 --> 00:43:06.660 align:middle line:90%
and lock the door.

00:43:06.660 --> 00:43:08.300 align:middle line:90%
I mean it was really scary.

00:43:08.300 --> 00:43:10.320 align:middle line:84%
Because sometimes she would
come in the middle the night,

00:43:10.320 --> 00:43:11.690 align:middle line:84%
and start hitting
us, and mostly me.

00:43:11.690 --> 00:43:12.970 align:middle line:90%
I was the oldest.

00:43:12.970 --> 00:43:15.500 align:middle line:84%
And then when she was
in the mental hospital

00:43:15.500 --> 00:43:18.030 align:middle line:84%
my father was
sexually abusing me.

00:43:18.030 --> 00:43:20.000 align:middle line:84%
He'd take me and
put me in this bed.

00:43:20.000 --> 00:43:20.735 align:middle line:90%
Oh my god.

00:43:20.735 --> 00:43:24.350 align:middle line:84%
And in those days
you could not tell.

00:43:24.350 --> 00:43:26.980 align:middle line:84%
You just-- and especially
when you're threatened.

00:43:26.980 --> 00:43:29.940 align:middle line:90%
You just can't tell.

00:43:29.940 --> 00:43:32.250 align:middle line:90%
And it was horrific.

00:43:32.250 --> 00:43:35.280 align:middle line:84%
And those scars,
especially from my father,

00:43:35.280 --> 00:43:37.580 align:middle line:84%
you would think the worst
would be the physical violence.

00:43:37.580 --> 00:43:42.400 align:middle line:84%
But especially from my father,
those scars went so deep.

00:43:42.400 --> 00:43:46.090 align:middle line:90%
And he-- he had cancer.

00:43:46.090 --> 00:43:50.060 align:middle line:84%
And-- and I got a phone
call that he was dying.

00:43:50.060 --> 00:43:53.720 align:middle line:84%
And I kept wanting
him to apologize.

00:43:53.720 --> 00:43:55.760 align:middle line:84%
I knew how deep those
wounds in me were.

00:43:55.760 --> 00:43:59.520 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, if he
apologizes then I can heal.

00:43:59.520 --> 00:44:00.694 align:middle line:90%
And I was so excited.

00:44:00.694 --> 00:44:01.960 align:middle line:84%
Because, I mean,
this sounds terrible.

00:44:01.960 --> 00:44:02.659 align:middle line:90%
He's dying.

00:44:02.659 --> 00:44:04.410 align:middle line:84%
And I'm thinking, oh
I can finally heal.

00:44:04.410 --> 00:44:05.640 align:middle line:90%
But that was what was true.

00:44:05.640 --> 00:44:06.420 align:middle line:90%
Of course, yes.

00:44:06.420 --> 00:44:08.030 align:middle line:84%
And so I'm on the
plane, and thinking I

00:44:08.030 --> 00:44:12.190 align:middle line:84%
can finally heal those wounds
from that childhood abuse.

00:44:12.190 --> 00:44:13.990 align:middle line:90%
And I got off the plane.

00:44:13.990 --> 00:44:17.490 align:middle line:84%
And someone came up to me
at the airport and said,

00:44:17.490 --> 00:44:18.522 align:middle line:90%
well he's dead.

00:44:18.522 --> 00:44:21.370 align:middle line:84%
And I thought,
well he can't die.

00:44:21.370 --> 00:44:22.274 align:middle line:90%
I have to heal.

00:44:22.274 --> 00:44:23.040 align:middle line:90%
I need to finish this.

00:44:23.040 --> 00:44:24.550 align:middle line:90%
I have to finish this.

00:44:24.550 --> 00:44:25.851 align:middle line:84%
And so I said, well,
I want to see him.

00:44:25.851 --> 00:44:26.616 align:middle line:90%
And they said, well no.

00:44:26.616 --> 00:44:27.490 align:middle line:90%
He's going to be cremated.

00:44:27.490 --> 00:44:28.360 align:middle line:90%
You can't see him.

00:44:28.360 --> 00:44:29.770 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I'm
going to see him.

00:44:29.770 --> 00:44:32.160 align:middle line:90%
And he was in a warehouse.

00:44:32.160 --> 00:44:35.310 align:middle line:84%
When I arrived at the warehouse,
they didn't want me in.

00:44:35.310 --> 00:44:36.700 align:middle line:84%
They said, well
you can't see him.

00:44:36.700 --> 00:44:37.930 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I'm
going to see him.

00:44:37.930 --> 00:44:40.410 align:middle line:84%
And eventually I was
pretty insistent,

00:44:40.410 --> 00:44:43.660 align:middle line:84%
I went back to this little
room that was fluorescent lit.

00:44:43.660 --> 00:44:46.890 align:middle line:84%
There was an old
wooden crate to sit on.

00:44:46.890 --> 00:44:49.640 align:middle line:90%
And there was my dead father.

00:44:49.640 --> 00:44:53.560 align:middle line:84%
Now when he was alive, I
never liked him to touch me.

00:44:53.560 --> 00:44:54.800 align:middle line:90%
It really-- it made me nauseous.

00:44:54.800 --> 00:44:57.040 align:middle line:84%
It activated all those
childhood memories.

00:44:57.040 --> 00:44:58.100 align:middle line:90%
I understand.

00:44:58.100 --> 00:45:01.910 align:middle line:84%
But for the first time
ever, I touched him.

00:45:01.910 --> 00:45:06.510 align:middle line:84%
And I touched his cold hands,
and his toes and his forehead.

00:45:06.510 --> 00:45:12.750 align:middle line:84%
And then all of a sudden
I started screaming.

00:45:12.750 --> 00:45:14.950 align:middle line:84%
And I can imagine the people in
the warehouse like, oh my gosh!

00:45:14.950 --> 00:45:15.649 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

00:45:15.649 --> 00:45:19.040 align:middle line:84%
And I screamed like, how could
you do that to a little girl?

00:45:19.040 --> 00:45:20.050 align:middle line:90%
How could you?

00:45:20.050 --> 00:45:21.080 align:middle line:90%
And I'm screaming.

00:45:21.080 --> 00:45:24.020 align:middle line:84%
And at one point I had to
get a subsequent surgery

00:45:24.020 --> 00:45:25.900 align:middle line:90%
after the original surgery.

00:45:25.900 --> 00:45:26.950 align:middle line:90%
And I didn't have any money.

00:45:26.950 --> 00:45:28.810 align:middle line:84%
And the doctor said, if
you don't get this surgery,

00:45:28.810 --> 00:45:29.680 align:middle line:90%
you'll die.

00:45:29.680 --> 00:45:31.490 align:middle line:84%
And I asked him if he could
help me with the surgery.

00:45:31.490 --> 00:45:33.610 align:middle line:84%
He goes, well I hope
you can find some money.

00:45:33.610 --> 00:45:35.920 align:middle line:84%
And I'm like, how can you
say that to your daughter?

00:45:35.920 --> 00:45:37.060 align:middle line:90%
She's going to die without this.

00:45:37.060 --> 00:45:39.320 align:middle line:90%
I'm screaming and screaming.

00:45:39.320 --> 00:45:42.670 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden, I
just felt like a balloon

00:45:42.670 --> 00:45:43.450 align:middle line:90%
that had deflated.

00:45:43.450 --> 00:45:48.170 align:middle line:84%
It was like-- and the whole
room seemed to glow golden.

00:45:48.170 --> 00:45:52.370 align:middle line:84%
And I said out loud, I don't
even know if I believe this.

